# Larger/denser fixed-shape throughput benchmark: fcc lattice (controlled density),
# no initial velocity -> dummy forces ~0 -> atoms stay put -> neighbor list fixed ->
# CUDA-graph replays every step. __A__ (lattice constant, A), __NC__ (cells/dim),
# __CORE_PT__, __NSTEPS__ substituted by run_md_sweep.sh. Atoms = 4*__NC__^3 (fcc).
units metal
atom_style atomic
boundary p p p

lattice fcc __A__
region box block 0 __NC__ 0 __NC__ 0 __NC__
create_box 2 box
create_atoms 1 box
mass 1 1.008
mass 2 15.999

neighbor 1.0 bin
neigh_modify every 1 delay 0 check yes

pair_style mff/torch 5.0 cuda
pair_coeff * * __CORE_PT__ H O

fix 1 all nve
thermo 100
thermo_style custom step temp pe
run __NSTEPS__
